@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @SatoshiLite Mining $DOGE and trading it for Bitcoin quickly became marginally profitable shortly after trading began. Most GPU miners switched to other coins, with Ethereum being the most popular.

@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @SatoshiLite In 2013, Jackson Palmer and Billy Markus created $DOGE as a meme coin. I was an early miner of DOGE. It was a funny joke and it allowed thousands of people who were priced out of Bitcoin mining to mine Bitcoin in a roundabout way.

@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 That’s incorrect. Let me explain to you why $DOGE exists. Back in 2010, Lazlo invented GPU mining for #Bitcoin. Advances in ASICs quickly made GPU mining for Bitcoin obsolete. Miners now had millions of dollars of obsolete hardware.
@techiedivas @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @ClayLambert20 The people who sell you the $ETH, $DOGE, and $ADA will trade your dollars  for #Bitcoin.

@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 Collective belief isn’t enough. #Bitcoin has properties that make it a serious competitor to become a global reserve asset. $DOGE does not have those properties.
